@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms & Conditions";
}

<section class="charity-hero">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="menu-hero-title">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
        <p class="charity-hero-subtitle">
            Please read these terms carefully before using the Noosh website, Rewards programme, or placing an order.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="terms-section py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="terms-card">
            <h2>1. General Terms</h2>
            <p>
                By accessing or using this website, you agree to be bound by these Terms &amp; Conditions.
                Noosh reserves the right to update these terms at any time; continued use of the site
                after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
            </p>

            <h2>2. Ordering</h2>
            <p>
                Menu items, prices, and availability are subject to change without notice. Orders placed
                through third-party delivery partners (such as Uber Eats or Mr D Food) are also subject to
                that platform's own terms and conditions. Noosh reserves the right to refuse or cancel any
                order at its discretion, including in cases of suspected fraud or unavailability of stock.
            </p>

            <h2>3. Noosh Rewards</h2>
            <p>
                The Noosh Rewards programme is free to join via phone number verification. Points are
                awarded at Noosh's discretion and have no cash value. Reward milestones and point
                thresholds may be changed at any time. Noosh reserves the right to suspend or terminate
                a Rewards account in cases of suspected abuse.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Privacy</h2>
            <p>
                Personal information collected through this website (such as phone numbers, names, and
                order details) is used solely to operate the Rewards programme, process catering and
                career applications, and improve our service. Noosh does not sell personal information to
                third parties. For any privacy-related queries, please contact us directly.
            </p>

            <hr class="terms-divider" />

            <h2 class="terms-policy-heading">Refund, Returns &amp; Customer Complaints Policy</h2>
            <p>
                At Noosh, we are committed to serving fresh, high-quality meals and providing exceptional
                customer service. Every meal is freshly prepared to order using quality ingredients and
                prepared in accordance with our food safety standards.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you experience an issue with your order, we encourage you to contact us as soon as
                possible. We will assess your complaint fairly and work towards an appropriate resolution.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Reporting a Complaint</h2>
            <p>
                If you believe there is an issue with your order, please contact us as soon as reasonably
                possible. To assist us with our investigation, please provide:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your order number or proof of purchase</li>
                <li>The store where your order was placed</li>
                <li>The date and approximate time of purchase</li>
                <li>A description of the issue</li>
                <li>Photographs of the product, where available</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Providing accurate information will assist us in resolving your complaint promptly.</p>

            <h2>6. Assessment of Complaints</h2>
            <p>Every complaint is assessed individually based on the information available.</p>
            <p>As part of our review, we may consider:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Order records</li>
                <li>Product preparation records</li>
                <li>Food safety records</li>
                <li>CCTV footage, where available</li>
                <li>Photographs</li>
                <li>Information provided by our team</li>
                <li>Any other relevant information</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                <strong>Submitting a complaint does not automatically entitle a customer to a replacement,
                voucher, store credit or refund.</strong> Each complaint is assessed on its own merits before
                an appropriate resolution is determined.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Wrong Orders</h2>
            <p>
                If you receive the incorrect meal or item, we will verify your order and, where appropriate,
                provide one or more of the following:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>A replacement meal</li>
                <li>A replacement item</li>
                <li>Store credit</li>
                <li>A Noosh voucher</li>
                <li>A refund, where appropriate</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>8. Missing Items</h2>
            <p>
                If an item is missing from your order, we will verify the order and provide the missing
                item or another appropriate resolution.
            </p>

            <h2>9. Incorrect Customisation</h2>
            <p>
                If your meal does not match the toppings, exclusions or heat level requested, we will
                investigate the matter. Where the error is confirmed, we may remake the meal, replace
                the affected item, provide store credit, issue a voucher or offer another appropriate remedy.
            </p>

            <h2>10. Food Quality</h2>
            <p>
                If your meal does not meet our quality standards, such as burnt products, stale chips or
                incorrectly prepared food, we will investigate the concern. Where a quality issue is
                confirmed, we will provide an appropriate remedy.
            </p>

            <h2>11. Food Safety</h2>
            <p>
                Food safety is our highest priority. If you believe your meal contains a foreign object, is
                spoiled or is otherwise unsafe for consumption, please notify us immediately. To assist
                with our investigation, we may request:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>The remaining product</li>
                <li>Original packaging</li>
                <li>Photographs</li>
                <li>Proof of purchase</li>
                <li>Medical documentation, where applicable</li>
                <li>Laboratory results, where appropriate</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Where a food safety issue is confirmed, Noosh will take appropriate corrective action and
                provide a suitable remedy in accordance with applicable consumer protection legislation.
            </p>

            <h2>12. Freshly Prepared Meals</h2>
            <p>
                Every Noosh meal is freshly prepared to order and is intended to be enjoyed as soon as
                possible after collection or delivery. For the best quality and food safety, we recommend
                consuming your meal within one hour of receiving it.
            </p>
            <p>
                Once food has left our premises, factors beyond our control, including storage,
                transportation, reheating and handling, may affect its quality and safety. Noosh cannot
                accept responsibility for meals consumed after an unreasonable delay or where the quality
                of the product has been affected by circumstances beyond our control.
            </p>

            <h2>13. Delayed Consumption</h2>
            <p>Complaints relating to meals that have been:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Left in a vehicle</li>
                <li>Stored at room temperature for an extended period</li>
                <li>Refrigerated or reheated</li>
                <li>Transported by the customer</li>
                <li>Consumed several hours after collection or delivery</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                may not qualify for a replacement or refund, as we cannot guarantee product quality once
                the meal is no longer under our control.
            </p>

            <h2>14. Taste Complaints</h2>
            <p>
                Taste is subjective and may vary between individuals. If you believe your meal tasted
                different from expected, we will gladly investigate the concern. However, refunds or
                compensation will only be considered where a genuine preparation error, product defect
                or food safety issue is identified.
            </p>

            <h2>15. Fully Consumed Meals</h2>
            <p>
                If a meal has been completely consumed and no evidence remains, we may be unable to
                verify the complaint. Where a complaint cannot reasonably be verified, we may be unable
                to provide compensation.
            </p>

            <h2>16. Orders Placed Through Delivery Platforms</h2>
            <p>
                Orders placed through third-party delivery platforms are subject to the terms and
                conditions of the respective delivery provider. Noosh is responsible for the quality and
                preparation of the food up to the point at which the order is collected by the delivery
                partner. The delivery platform is responsible for matters relating to the delivery service,
                including:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Delivery times</li>
                <li>Driver delays</li>
                <li>Driver conduct</li>
                <li>Route selection</li>
                <li>Handling of the order after collection</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Customers who place orders through a third-party delivery platform should submit
                complaints through that platform in the first instance. Where a complaint relates
                specifically to the preparation or quality of the food, Noosh will work with the delivery
                platform to investigate and resolve the matter where appropriate.
            </p>

            <h2>17. Refunds</h2>
            <p>Customer satisfaction is important to us. Where appropriate, we will first consider:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Preparing a fresh replacement meal</li>
                <li>Replacing the affected item</li>
                <li>Store credit</li>
                <li>A Noosh voucher</li>
                <li>Another reasonable remedy</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Refunds are considered a last resort and will generally only be provided where:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Goods are unsafe</li>
                <li>Goods are defective</li>
                <li>Goods are not of acceptable quality</li>
                <li>Goods are unfit for their intended purpose</li>
                <li>A refund is required under applicable consumer protection legislation</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Approved refunds will ordinarily be processed to the original method of payment.</p>

            <h2>18. Goodwill Gestures</h2>
            <p>
                From time to time, Noosh may choose to provide a replacement meal, voucher, store credit
                or another goodwill gesture, even where we are not legally required to do so. Any goodwill
                gesture is offered entirely at Noosh's discretion, does not constitute an admission of
                liability and does not create a precedent for future claims.
            </p>

            <h2>19. Allergens</h2>
            <p>
                Our kitchens handle ingredients including gluten, dairy, eggs, sesame and other common
                allergens. While we take reasonable precautions to minimise cross-contact, we cannot
                guarantee that any product is completely free from allergens. Customers with severe
                allergies should exercise their own judgement before purchasing.
            </p>

            <h2>20. Fraudulent or Unverifiable Claims</h2>
            <p>
                Claims that cannot reasonably be verified, or that are found to be false, dishonest or
                fraudulent, may be declined. Repeated fraudulent or abusive complaints may result in
                future claims being refused.
            </p>

            <h2>21. Consumer Rights</h2>
            <p>
                Nothing contained in this policy limits or excludes any rights available to consumers under
                the Consumer Protection Act, 68 of 2008, or any other applicable legislation.
            </p>

            <h2>22. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
                If you have any questions or concerns regarding your order, please contact our Customer
                Care team.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:customercare@noosheatery.co.za">customercare@noosheatery.co.za</a></p>
            <p>Please include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Your order number or proof of purchase</li>
                <li>Store location</li>
                <li>Date and time of purchase</li>
                <li>A description of the issue</li>
                <li>Supporting photographs, where available</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                Our team will acknowledge your complaint promptly and aim to resolve it as quickly and
                fairly as possible.
            </p>

            <p class="terms-updated">
                Last updated: July 2026. This policy may be amended from time to time to reflect changes
                in our operations, products, services or applicable legislation. The most current version
                will always be available on our website and official communication channels.
                <br />© 2026 Noosh. All Rights Reserved.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>